  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 0644da355aa0fa14983545f2d60c0c31, type: 3}
  m_Name: Slipup
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  questionText: Say a slipup or a mistake happens on scene while we're shooting.
    How will you react?
  traitsRevealed:
  - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8c6e1d8a00f4b6f48b27a51cccd85dde, type: 2}
  - {fileID: 11400000, guid: e32f82a8049dce847a95d691a3f9b90f, type: 2}
  - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 662bceae056a0684fab5068a6dea6e1c, type: 2}
  defaultReply: Well, honestly, I'd have to stop and we'd have to restart the scene.
  replyKey:
  - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8c6e1d8a00f4b6f48b27a51cccd85dde, type: 2}
  - {fileID: 11400000, guid: e32f82a8049dce847a95d691a3f9b90f, type: 2}
  - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 662bceae056a0684fab5068a6dea6e1c, type: 2}
  - {fileID: 11400000, guid: dfa441996a5f7f54398da0de2558ff37, type: 2}
  - {fileID: 11400000, guid: c0fd7b2700683214b885b176ece1c144, type: 2}
  - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 13e2e1621147f9040bc80873b3bb4c0e, type: 2}
  replyText:
  - I'd try to keep it going. I'm used to these situations and honestly, it sometimes
    leads to better scenes.
  - I'd do my best to ignore it and keep going. A single misstep isn't so bad.
  - I actually don't know what I would do, but I know it would be my fault so apologies
    in advance.
  - Well, I'd go reapply deoderant since I probably got sweaty from shooting.
  - I don't know... start crying, maybe?
  - I have a feeling that would be my fault. I'd probably be messing up my lines
    so much.
